# Testing Report Summary

## 🧱 Project: Task Manager CLI
**Goal:** Practice writing and running unit tests using Jest for basic task management logic.

---

## ✅ What I Tested
1. **addTask()** — verified that multiple tasks can be added successfully.
2. **deleteTask()** — checked the system’s behavior when deleting the same task twice.
3. **getAllTasks()** — confirmed it returns an empty list when no tasks exist.
4. **getCompletedTasks()** — ensured only completed tasks are listed.

---

## 🐞 Observed Issues
- [Issue 001 – Deleting a task twice throws error](https://github.com/wambuachris38/taskmanager/issues/1)
- [Issue 002 – getCompletedTasks returns incorrect data](https://github.com/wambuachris38/taskmanager/issues/2)

---

## 🧪 Example Test Cases Written
```javascript
test('should add multiple tasks correctly', () => {
  const taskManager = new TaskManager();
  taskManager.addTask('Buy milk');
  taskManager.addTask('Read book');
  expect(taskManager.getAllTasks().length).toBe(2);
});

test('should handle deleting a task twice gracefully', () => {
  const taskManager = new TaskManager();
  taskManager.addTask('Buy milk');
  taskManager.deleteTask(1);
  expect(() => taskManager.deleteTask(1)).toThrow();
});
